          <h3>Manuscript Submission Guidelines:</h3>
          <hr class='hidHr'>
          <ul class='col subUl'>
            <li>Submit an email to mquills@mquills.com, and list the title of your work in the subject line.</li>
              <br>
            <li>Your work will be evaluated for meeting our Ethical Standards (see right), as well as meeting a 
                minimum amount of quality.</li>
                <br>
            <li>Be sure to proofread your work. Submissions with excessive typos or grammatical errors will be 
                rejected.</li>
                <br>
            <li>Please send the complete manuscript for your work with your query letter (email) 
                as an attached DOC (.doc) file. We receive a lot of manuscripts, and unfortunately cannot correspond with 
                authors before we have evaluated a work. This means that if only a chapter is sent, or if the manuscript 
                is not attached in some way, the query may be deleted. We only accept completed, unpublished works.</li>
                <br>
            <li>As a part of your email, be sure to include your name, your work's word count, a brief summary of 
                the plot, and any links or publication credits you may have.</li>
                <br>
            <li>We will try to respond within one month of submitting your query if we are considering it.</li>
                <br>
            <li>We do not accept submissions from authors for whom English is a second language (with which 
                they are not fluent) when those manuscripts have not been at least proof read by a native English speaker.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class='subCol col col100'>
          <h3>Ethical Standards:</h3>
          <br>
          <p> <strong>No disinformation:</strong> Health, metaphysical, spiritual or other works must not make claims that 
              are dubious or false.
              <br>
              <br>
              <strong>No illegal content:</strong> No incitements to violence, harassment, etc.
              <br>
              <br>
              <strong>"R Rated" or tamer:</strong> We do not accept submissions with excessive sex or gore. Submissions should 
              be, at most, only as graphic as one would expect of an R rated film.
          </p>
        </div>
